description: A machine-learning framework that predicts Ultimate Tensile Strength (UTS) of steels using composition + heat-treatment + processing parameters. The dataset is synthetically generated using metallurgy-based rules (HallPetch, tempering response, quenching behavior, composition strengthening).
In this part, we work with machine learning frameworks, such as Scikit-learn orNumpy.

Genex is a full-stack application designed to assist doctors in predicting autoimmune diseases and managing personalized treatment plans. The system uses machine learning on patient gene expression data and integrates a digital twin framework to simulate drug-gene and drug-drug interactions, helping clinicians make informed therapeutic decisions.

A collection of deep learning models, training pipelines, experiments, and utilities built using modern machine learning frameworks. This repository includes clean, modular implementations of popular neural network architectures, along with reproducible training scripts, experiment tracking, and tools for data processing.

Machine Learning Framework for Identifying Lymph Node Metastasis Biomarkers in Breast Cancer. This repository provides an end-to-end workflow integrating differential expression analysis, machine learningbased feature selection, survival modelling, and external biological validation for robust biomarker discovery.

A lightweight and modular Model Extractor tool for loading, analyzing, and exporting machine-learning models. Supports extracting model layers, parameters, weights, metadata, and architecture summaries from frameworks like PyTorch or TensorFlow. Ideal for ML engineers who need to inspect, debug, convert, or document model structures.

This project contains a set of **Jupyter notebooks** to help students and data scientists deeply understand and visualize the *four main classification metrics* used in machine learning: **Accuracy, Precision, Recall, and F1 Score**.
A machine learning framework to proactively forecast the Air Quality Index (AQI) in Indian cities using temporal feature engineering and a generalized XGBoost model.

A full-stack machine learning project demonstrating image classification using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) trained on the CIFAR-10 dataset, deployed as a user-friendly web application with Python's Flask framework.

Enwar is an LLM framework that processes multi-modal inputs, transforms them into textual representations, and in parallel pipelines that data to a set of machine learning models to complete specific tasks. Within this scope, the data inputs are pushed to a perception agent.

Attention-guided deep learning framework for multi-class brain tumor classification using MRI scans. Combines EfficientNetB3 with CBAM for high accuracy (99.29%) and integrates Explainable AI (HiResCAM) for visual interpretability of predictions.

Capstone project for the Imperial College London AI & Machine Learning Certificate, showcasing end-to-end ML development  from data preparation to model training, evaluation, and insights using Python and modern ML frameworks.

A robust machine learning framework for Credit Risk Modeling. Implements SMOTE for class imbalance and compares Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, LightGBM, and XGBoost. Optimized via threshold tuning to identify high-risk demographic and behavioral profiles.

Pax is a Jax-based machine learning framework for training large scale models. Pax allows for advanced and fully configurable experimentation and parallelization, and has demonstrated industry leading model flop utilization rates.
Thesis project on phishing detection using Machine Learning

A federated learning platform for training diffusion models on distributed sensitive healthcare data to produce high-fidelity synthetic datasets without raw data leaving source nodes. Built with Flower (FL framework), PyTorch, and Opacus (DP).

A reproducible framework for probabilistic decision modeling and simulation in high-volatility time series. Demonstrates how to use statistical indicators, machine learning classifiers, and automated workflows to test and evaluate data-driven decision rules under uncertainty.

This repository contains the full-stack code for a serverless, real-time water quality monitoring system. An ESP32 microcontroller sends sensor data (pH, turbidity, etc.) to a serverless backend on AWS, which processes the data, runs a machine learning model, stores it in DynamoDB. A dynamic web frontend then visualizes this data on a Leaflet map.

Repository for the paper Machine Learning-Based Prediction and Geometric Quality Assessment in 3D Concrete Printing. Includes experimental data, preprocessing scripts, CatBoost/DecisionTree ML models, and code for printability maps and geometric quality metrics in 3DCP.

AI-driven discovery of Metal Organic Frameworks (MOFs) for efficient CO capture from cement plants and catalytic conversion into methanol using solar energy. Includes datasets, preprocessing scripts, machine learning models, and analysis notebooks.

This project Predicts plant health using NDVI values, classifying leaves as Healthy, Unhealthy, or Dead. TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning framework developed by Google. It provides strong support for various platforms, especially Linux, and is widely adopted in the industry due to its active community and production-ready capabilities.

A comprehensive repository for automatic hyperparameter tuning libraries, tools, and tutorials. This serves as a knowledge base for finding, comparing, and utilizing state-of-the-art hyperparameter optimization techniques to improve model performance across various machine learning frameworks.

This project develops neural-network surrogate models for fast, accurate European option pricing under stochastic volatility frameworks. Traditional methods like Monte Carlo simulations are computationally expensive. The goal is to use machine learning models, trained on synthetic data, for orders-of-magnitude faster pricing with similar accuracy.

Cerebrus is an intelligent malware analysis framework designed to provide multi-layered defense against modern cyber threats. It integrates static analysis, machine learning, external threat intelligence, and explainable AI (XAI) to deliver a robust platform for detecting known and unknown malware across various file formats.
